# Part 6: Docker Configuration

Pulled Docker images for WordPress and MySQL.

```bash
sudo docker pull mysql:latest
sudo docker pull wordpress:latest

Ran containers:

sudo docker run -d --name mysql-container \
  -e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=StrongPass123 \
  -e MYSQL_DATABASE=wordpress \
  mysql:latest

sudo docker run -d --name wordpress-container \
  -p 80:80 \
  -e WORDPRESS_DB_HOST=mysql-container:3306 \
  -e WORDPRESS_DB_USER=root \
  -e WORDPRESS_DB_PASSWORD=StrongPass123 \
  -e WORDPRESS_DB_NAME=wordpress \
  --link mysql-container:mysql \
  wordpress:latest
Accessed WordPress setup via EC2 Public IP.

 Screenshot: wordpress page.png
